This article is about Executive Order 13590, signed by President Barack Obama on November 21, 2011. The order authorizes the imposition of certain sanctions on individuals or entities that provide goods, services, technology, or support to Iran's energy and petrochemical sectors. The Secretary of State, in consultation with other officials, is authorized to impose sanctions on those who sell, lease, or provide goods, services, technology, or support to Iran that have a fair market value of $1,000,000 or more and could contribute to Iran's ability to develop petroleum resources or expand its domestic production of petrochemical products. The order also imposes restrictions on financial institutions and prohibits certain transactions and donations. The Secretary of the Treasury, in consultation with the Secretary of State, is authorized to take necessary actions to implement the sanctions. The order is effective from November 21, 2011.